  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions and certain businesses are typically required to:\n\n1. Implement anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n2. Report suspicious transactions to financial intelligence units\n3. Conduct customer due diligence\n4. Maintain transaction records\n5. Train employees to recognize potential money laundering activities\n\nHowever, specific details can vary by jurisdiction. Consulting legal professionals is recommended for precise guidance.",
